recruit /rɪˈkruːt/

(recruiting,recruited,recruits) 

1. V-T If you recruit people for an organization, you select them and persuade them to join it or work for it. 招收; 招募 

例： The police are trying to recruit more black and Hispanic officers. 警方正试图招收更多的黑人和西班牙裔的警官。 

例： She set up her stand to recruit students to the Anarchist Association. 她搭了一个摊位招募学生加入无政府主义者协会。 

2. recruiting N-UNCOUNT 招收; 招募 

例： A bomb exploded at an army recruiting office. 一枚炸弹在一个征兵办公室爆炸了。 

3. N-COUNT A recruit is a person who has recently joined an organization or an army. 新成员; 新兵 

例： ...a new recruit to the LA Police Department. …洛杉矶警察局的一名新警员。

